    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_jproteome_5c00435__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses mzPeak design vision and roadmap but does not mention a Rust command-line converter tool, a mzpeak_prototyping repository, or specific input format conversion mechanisms. The paper states mzPeak will be 'released with a reference implementation in a low level programming language (e.g., C++) with bindings for multiple programming languages (e.g., Python)' \u2014 not Rust. No mention of a CLI converter tool exists in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-5c00435",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "What are the input formats supported by the Rust command-line converter tool in the mzpeak_prototyping repository, and what is the mechanism by which it converts them into mzPeak output?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:16:26.196185+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_jproteome_5c00435__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "strategic partnerships will be established not only with major MS vendors but also with developers of existing \"keystone\" software, e.g., OpenMS, ProteoWizard, METASPACE",
      "asbval:note": "OpenMS is mentioned as a keystone software partner for adoption strategy, not as a tool used in the mzPeak implementation itself. The paper indicates OpenMS will be integrated with mzPeak (via converters/backends/wrappers) but does not describe OpenMS as part of the core mzPeak development or conversion mechanism.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-5c00435",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "OpenMS",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:16:26.196185+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_jproteome_5c00435__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly states reference implementation will be in 'a low level programming language (e.g., C++) with bindings for multiple programming languages (e.g., Python)' (passage 5). Rust is not mentioned anywhere in the paper as a development language for mzPeak.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-5c00435",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Rust",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:16:26.196185+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_jproteome_5c00435__task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzPeak is designed to overcome the limitations of the aforementioned formats by adopting a hybrid model that combines efficient binary storage for numerical data and human-readable metadata storage... The data storage model will be natively binary, allowing for random access to spectra, chromatograms, ion images, and mobilograms",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes mzPeak as a binary format with comprehensive metadata support, consistent with the expected output claim.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-5c00435",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "mzPeak binary output file with valid format structure and metadata",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:16:26.196185+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_jproteome_5c00435__task_001/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "the reference implementation will be designed to integrate with existing tools, minimizing disruptions to established workflows by providing converters, backends, or wrappers",
      "asbval:note": "Paper mentions that mzPeak will include converters for existing formats, but does not describe a specific CLI converter tool, does not name it as a Rust tool, and does not reference a mzpeak_prototyping repository. The paper discusses converters as part of the adoption strategy but not as a standalone reconstructible tool with documented input formats.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-5c00435",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct the mzPeak CLI Converter tool for transforming existing mass-spectrometry formats into mzPeak",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:16:26.196185+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
