      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The data storage model will be natively binary, allowing for random access to spectra, chromatograms, ion images, and mobilograms, ensuring efficiency in handling large and complex data sets. Vendors will also be able to store essential technical metadata, including but not limited to MS and LC settings and run-specific parameters.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms mzPeak will store spectrum data (m/z, intensities) and metadata in Parquet format. However, the paper does not describe or demonstrate actual output artifacts from reading mzPeak files, nor does it discuss CSV export or the specific columnar structure of parsed data. The expected output is inferred from the format design but not explicitly demonstrated.",
