    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/arrow-table-serialization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzPeak is designed to overcome the limitations of the aforementioned formats by adopting a hybrid model that combines efficient binary storage for numerical data and human-readable metadata storage... For initial implementation studies, we will use Parquet (https://parquet.apache.org/), an open source, data file format designed for efficient storage and retrieval... Designed with a native binary format, mzPeak will enable random access to spectra, chromatograms, ion images, and mobilograms, ensuring fast and efficient data retrieval.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes mzPeak's use of Parquet for serializing MS data including spectra and chromatograms. The research question aligns with the paper's core design goal.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-jproteome-5c00435",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
